commit: Back out a lot of crufty/hacky workaround code which isn't needed or helping, and keeps needing more interventions. It turns out that the issues that inspired all this crappy handling was google's internal system reporting usernames oddly, but which has been fixed for a long time, and edge-cases resulted in a lot of needless handling to be added. AT this point, it's all doing more harm than good.
Fix a problem where <user> is applied as a name, not an email, and therefore breaks the standard 'user <user@email.com>' format.
Fix the output of hte codebase creation log entry, which currently is pointing at the wrong object.
Possibly fix a bug in hte merge codebases directive, where the modified and destination codebases were inverted.  Detected by ErrorProne.
Fix a java style issue where we shoudl declare each variable separately.  Also fix some error prone findings.
Fix two error-prone findings about declaring each variable separately, and using implicit charset.
Fix a use-case in moe where git isn't returning a valid codebase, when it's being fetched from a tag.
Fix usages of generated AutoValue implementation classes that occur outside their AutoValue class definition.
Fix string formatting bugs in MOE
Stop throwing on a bad config (where people both use rename:use_regex=true, and try to use an inverse edior), until we can fix people forward
Fix permissions
Fix make-binary.sh now that the client is in a subfolder.
Fix original author processing to be more tolerant of bad author metadata.
Ease up on errors during codebase creation, while bookkeeping.
Improve error handling in SystemCommandRunner
Fix --db flag handling
Improve repository expression parse errors
Fix stray System.out that got past review. :/
A few minor fixes to moe (wording change, build file fix, etc).
MOE ProjectConfig errors on config files that have different semantics under GSON than under JavaScript.
Fix up github url processing so it's properly validating against the project configurations and reporting a reasonable error when that fails.
Add copyright and add some error checking.
Tweak the interim files generated and error messages.
